      <scopecontent id="aspace_35e26cdabe1e78dfff40c8c2c4d86f13">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists primarily of official documents of documents from the archives of the rabbinate of Tangier, Morocco, from the 1920s to the 1970s. The documents are thought to have been the possession of Grand Rabbi Yamin Cohen. They consist mostly of official rabbinical correspondence and legal documents from the Tangier rabbinate, the rabbinates of other Moroccan and foreign Jewish communities, and the successive Spanish, French, and Moroccan civil administrations. They deal with issues such as personal legal status (marriage, divorce), inheritance, and the transfer of real estate. Other documents pertain to the affairs of the Jewish communities of Tangier and other locations or the affairs of Grand Rabbi Yamin Cohen. The papers are arranged according to the location of their source.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
